      "text": "Section 5\nAmalfi Coast Finale, Pompeii & Return Home\nSunday, June 28\nPath of the Gods + Amalfi\nGoal For The Day\nExperience the famous Path of the Gods views without turning the honeymoon into an exhausting hiking\nexpedition.\nThis itinerary is intentionally designed for comfort.\nThe objective is:\nIncredible views\nMinimal hiking\nTime in Amalfi\nPlenty of relaxation back at the villa\nMorning\n7:00 AM\nWake up.\nBreakfast at Villa Gianlica.\nEat a real breakfast.\nBring:\nWater\nSunglasses\nHat\nComfortable sneakers\n- \n- \n- \n- \n- \n- \n- \n- \n1\n\nSunscreen\nPhone charger\nLeave beach gear behind.\nTransportation\nStep 1\nWalk to the nearest SITA bus stop along Via Guglielmo Marconi / SS163.\nStand on the:\nAmalfi-bound side\nStep 2\nBoard bus toward:\nAmalfi\nStep 3\nExit at:\nAmalfi Bus Terminal\nThis is the transportation hub for the area.\nTransfer To Bomerano\nAt Amalfi Bus Terminal:\nAsk:\n\"Bomerano?\"\nor\n- \n- \n2\n\n\"Path of the Gods?\"\nLocals are very familiar with this route.\nBoard bus toward:\nAgerola / Bomerano\nArrive Bomerano\nThis is the easiest access point to Path of the Gods.\nPath of the Gods Strategy\nRecommended Option A\nWalk only 20–30 minutes into the trail.\nStop frequently.\nTake photos.\nEnjoy the scenery.\nTurn around when satisfied.\nThere is absolutely no need to complete the entire hike.\nEstimated Hiking Time\n45–90 minutes total.\nPerfect for travelers who want the experience without committing to a major trek.\nReturn To Amalfi\nWalk back to Bomerano.\n3\n\nBoard return bus to Amalfi.\nAmalfi\nLunch\nKeep this simple.\nOption 1\nDa Gemma\nMost romantic.\nOption 2\nL'Abside\nBest balance.\nOption 3\nPasticceria Pansa\nLight lunch and pastries.\nAmalfi Highlights\nChoose only a few.\nDo not over-schedule.\nAmalfi Cathedral\nWorth seeing.\nBeautiful setting.\n4\n\nPiazza del Duomo\nSit.\nPeople watch.\nEnjoy a drink.\nShopping\nBrowse:\nLemon products\nCeramics\nSouvenirs\nLimit shopping to approximately one hour .\nReturn To Praiano\nGoal\nLeave Amalfi around:\n3:00 PM\nThis protects relaxation time.\nEvening\nBack at Villa Gianlica.\nRelax.\nNap.\nPool.\nBalcony.\n- \n- \n- \n5\n\nWine.\nSunset.\nDinner\nRecommended:\nVilla terrace evening.\nAlternative:\nKasai\nChe Bontà\nIl Pirata\nTomorrow is Capri.\nDo not stay out late.\nMonday, June 29\nCapri Boat Excursion\nGoal For The Day\nThis is the signature experience of the honeymoon.\nRelax.\nSwim.\nEnjoy the coastline.\nDo not worry about schedules once aboard.\n6\n\nMorning\n7:00 AM\nWake up.\nBreakfast at Villa Gianlica.\nBring:\nSwimsuit\nSunglasses\nSunscreen\nWaterproof pouch\nPhone charger\nDo not bring:\nLarge bags\nOutside food\nOutside drinks\nMarina Departure\n8:15 AM\nLeave Villa Gianlica.\nArrival Goal\n8:45 AM\nLocation:\nMarina di Praia\nTour Information\nOperator:\n- \n- \n- \n- \n- \n- \n- \n- \n7\n\nLa Bellavita Charter\nBooking:\nTour Time\n9:00 AM–5:00 PM\nIf Confused\nCall:\n+39 089 288 1694\nExpected Highlights\nPotential stops include:\nCapri coastline\nSwimming locations\nFaraglioni rocks\nMarina Piccola\nCapri town free time\nBlue Grotto Note\nEntry depends entirely on sea conditions.\nIf entry is unavailable:\nDo not be disappointed.\nThis is common and beyond anyone's control.\n- \n- \n- \n- \n- \n8\n\nReturn To Praiano\nApproximately:\n5:00 PM\nFinal Amalfi Coast Evening\nThis is your final night in Praiano.\nKeep it simple.\nKeep it memorable.\nRecommended Dinner\nChe Bontà takeaway.\nTake food back to villa.\nOpen wine.\nWatch sunset.\nPack luggage.\nEnjoy final Amalfi Coast views.\nPacking Reminder\nBefore bed verify:\n□ Passports\n□ Chargers\n□ AirPods\n□ Camera\n9\n\n□ Souvenirs\n□ Wallets\nTuesday, June 30\nPompeii Day\nGoal For The Day\nExperience Pompeii without exhausting yourselves.\nThis is the final full day of the honeymoon.\nMorning\nBreakfast at Villa Gianlica.\nFinish packing.\nCheck room carefully.\nTransfer\nVilla Gianlica → Moxy Pompeii\nPrivate transfer .\nQuoted:\n€160 total\nMoxy Pompeii\nAddress:\nVia Castriota 43\n10\n\nTorre Annunziata\nArrival\nIf room is not ready:\nLeave luggage with front desk.\nProceed directly to Pompeii.\nTransportation To Pompeii\nRecommended:\nBolt or taxi.\nDestination:\nPorta Marina Entrance\nPompeii Strategy\nDo NOT attempt to see everything.\nFocus on highlights.\nPriority Stops\nForum\nHeart of the city.\nTemple of Apollo\nOne of the oldest structures.\n11\n\nHouse of the Faun\nMost famous private residence.\nLarge Theatre\nBeautiful photo stop.\nGarden of the Fugitives\nMost emotional location in Pompeii.\nTotal Time\n3–4 hours maximum.\nWhen tired:\nLeave.\nThere is no prize for staying longer .\nReturn To Hotel\nCheck in.\nShower .\nRest.\nRecharge.\nFinal Honeymoon Dinner\nBosco de' Medici\nRecommended departure:\n12\n\n6:30 PM\nDinner:\n7:00 PM\nWhy This Restaurant\nIt feels celebratory without being overly formal.\nIt provides a memorable final honeymoon evening.\nIt strikes the perfect balance between romantic and relaxed.\nAfter Dinner\nReturn to hotel.\nFinish packing.\nCharge phones.\nSet alarms.\nGet to sleep early.\nTomorrow is departure day.\nWednesday, July 1\nReturn Home\nGoal For The Day\nGet to Naples Airport comfortably early.\nNo stress.\nNo rushing.\n13\n\nMorning\n5:45 AM\nWake up.\nFinal Room Check\nVerify:\n□ Passports\n□ Wallets\n□ Phones\n□ Chargers\n□ AirPods\n□ Souvenirs\n□ Boat photos\n□ Wedding items\nTransportation\n6:00 AM\nRequest Bolt.\nDestination:\nNaples International Airport\n14\n\nBackup Plan\nIf Bolt availability appears limited:\nAsk Moxy front desk Tuesday evening to arrange taxi service.\nDeparture\nGoal:\n6:15 AM\nAirport Arrival\nGoal:\n6:45–7:00 AM\nThis provides a comfortable buffer before departure.\nFlight\nDelta DL279\nNaples → Atlanta\nDeparture:\n9:05 AM\nArrival:\n2:31 PM\nNaples Airport Flow\nCheck luggage.1. \n15\n\nSecurity screening.\nPassport control.\nBreakfast.\nBoard flight.\nArrival In Atlanta\nAfter landing:\nImmigration\nCollect luggage\nCustoms\nExit arrivals area\nFinal Transportation\nRequest Uber after luggage is collected.\nDestination:\nWoodstock, Georgia\nHome\nThe honeymoon officially concludes.\nOver twelve days you experienced:\nParis\nThe Eiffel Tower\nThe Seine\nVersailles\nPraiano\nPositano\nAmalfi\nCapri\nPompeii\nMost importantly:\nYou experienced it together .\n2. \n3. \n4. \n5. \n1. \n2. \n3. \n4. \n- \n- \n- \n- \n- \n- \n- \n- \n- \n16\n\nEnd Of Daily Itinerary\nThe following sections of this guide contain:\nTransportation Appendix\nDining Guide\nPacking Guide\nTicket Tracker\nEmergency Information\nFinal Travel Tips\nThese sections are designed as quick-reference tools while traveling.\n- \n- \n- \n- \n- \n- \n17",
